{
  "stem": "293.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You're going with a train on the cliff of the mountain to get through the mountains on the south side of the mountains, and we come to Uzok.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This way, they took us back to the camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He said, oh, then you are from Uzok because I am from Uzok too.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And give us permission to stay but we didn't decide with my friends that I met in Budapest, and we were travelling together to go to Germany, to east-- from east to west Germany. you see?",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were starting to do in November.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we go on that, walking in through the mountains, in the deep snow, and we arrive beginning of December to-- across the West Germany borders, and we came a few days later to Munich.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then we saw our friends, Rosner and Schindler is there and everybody is there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we live together.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I stay over there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I am not a person what I will run around doing nothing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I decide to do something, so I report to the UNRRA, United Nations Relief Fund.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I told them what was my occupation and everything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I became education center director of UNRRA with [INAUDIBLE] in Munich, with a job to organize and get children to schools.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Nobody could organize.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I brought 1,700 children to school, promising in their papers that I will give them clothes, food, shelter, and education.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the parents, if they were not orphans, the parents can go and arrange a transfer to other countries or to emigrate to America, or to South America, to-- back to their own country.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I have, since 1945, in December, till April 1947, 1,700 children.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I'm giving them diploma, graduating from high school, graduating from public school.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
